    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trees considered to have supernatural powers, curative properties, or ritual significance, often marked by affixing rags or other objects on their branches. Trees venerated in this way are not specific to any culture or period.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000132/Suzzallo-UW</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052228/Dafni, Rituals, Ceremonies and Customs Related to Sacred Trees with a Special Reference to the Middle East, Journal of Ethnobiology and Ethnomedicine (2007)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bomen met een rituele betekenis of veronderstelde bovennatuurlijke of helende krachten, vaak aangegeven door lappen stof of andere objecten aan hun takken te hangen. In vele culturen en periodes zijn bomen als heilig vereerd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>被認為具有超自然力量、醫療作用或具有宗教意義的樹，通常會有布條或其他物件綁在樹枝上。許多文化或時代都有此種敬拜樹木的表現。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
